-- Coca-Cola plans to invest $5 billion in India by 2020
-- 
-- Tue Jun 26, 2012 6:46am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/06/26/us-cocacola-india-idUSBRE85P0AR20120626

 

 NEW DELHI  (Reuters) - Coca-Cola Co ( KO.N ), the world's largest soft-drinks maker, plans to invest $5 billion in India by 2020, Chairman Muhtar Kent said in the Indian capital on Tuesday. 
 Last November, the company had said it plans to invest $2 billion in India over the next five years to expand its non-alcoholic, ready-to-drink business in India. (Reporting by  Anurag Kotoky )